						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Kreese wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">This sounds promising. The limitation of songs in Vegaplay has been a problem for me.</div><br /> Same here, it was my motivation. I hope it will be useful, if people would like a 512K build it's not too much of an issue. The main thing I wanted was a 'no fuss' tool to put music on real hardware. <br /> I haven't changed the UI very much so there is lots of room there for improvement, but OTH I'm considering turning the PPU off during playback for the best sync timing. I'm finishing up a HW Midi Clock to Sync24 interface and after some testing will know how much NMI calls affect the playback.<br />Yogi</div>

