			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It might be a timing difference ultimately resulting from  a difference in PPU/CPU alignment between the Famicom and NES. Anything that affects PPU/CPU alignment is likely to affect 6502/APU alignment within the CPU because normally, the program running on the 6502 waits for the PPU to warm up before doing anything. I know the PPU reset line isn't connected one way on the front-loading NES and the other way on the Famicom and top-loading NES.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
